Can't start service with Docker Version 4.11.0 (83626)

That's happen on TRAEFIK_DASHBOARD_USER at .env file which is the value contains $ character. And docker recognized it as variable, that's why we found The "lXaL3lj6raFic6rFqr2" variable is not set error message. You could pull the latest update from Laradock which add quotation for TRAEFIK_DASHBOARD_USER variable on .env.example file or just manually add single quote on TRAEFIK_DASHBOARD_USER variable.
